==Broadcasting rights==
*'''United Kingdom''': Live coverage of selected matches has been shown on terrestrial channel [[Five (TV)|Five]], formerly known as [[Channel 5]]. Delayed coverage is usually shared between Five and [[satellite]]/[[cable television|cable]] network British [[Eurosport]]. Seen as a lower key event, the Confederations Cup has never been shown on main [[BBC]] and [[ITV]] channels. The rights are generally bought up quietly, around six months before the main event for much less money than the [[FIFA World Cup]].
*In '''Italy''' RAI must, by law, broadcast the ''[[Italy national football team|Azzurri]]'' matches, therefore the state broadcaster is very likely to buy part of the rights (if not all of them, since they are cheaper than the World Cup ones) for the Confederations Cup when Italy participates.

